-- Arabtec CEO Appointed to Depa Director in Board Changes
-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 2013-05-15T07:17:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-15/arabtec-ceo-appointed-to-depa-director-in-board-changes.html
Hasan Abdullah Ismaik, the chief
executive officer of  Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC) , has been appointed a
director on the board of  Depa Ltd. (DEPA)  as the Dubai-based interiors
contractor reshuffled its board.  The new board also comprises Fawz Al Hokair, Khaldoun
Tabari, Mohammed Al Fahim, Wassul Fakhoury, Iyad AbdulRahim
and Marwan Shehadeh, Depa  said in a statement  to Nasdaq Dubai
today on its shareholders’ resolution. Al Fahim and Fakhoury are
also on the board of Arabtec, according to information on the
company’s website.  Shareholders approved the removal of Riad Kamal, who is a
board member of Arabtec, and Orhan Osmansoy from the board.
Shareholders didn’t approve resolutions to reappoint Faisal Al
Matrook, Chris Foll and Ahmad Ramadan, according to the Depa
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
